<item>
            <title>[LU-17460] sanity-lnet test_214 causes a netdevice reference leak with IPv6</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17460</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt; If the destination NID to the ping commands is IPv6, then the fake interface cannot be cleaned up. A message like the following is seen:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;      Message from syslogd@el8-mds1 at Dec  4 15:58:11 ...
        kernel:unregister_netdevice: waiting for test1pg to become free. Usage count = 15
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
